\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {\textup  {\textsc  {ROAR}}{} overview.} A dense single-run trajectory is reduced to a near-optimal, barrier-filtered candidate set. \textup  {\textsc  {ROAR}}{} then directly optimizes KL-ball robust risk over simplex weights on that set and deploys a single weight soup. The paper's main point is that the optimized post-hoc objective is the same object that appears in the theory.}}{3}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
